      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(qa-lab): prevent child process signal bleeding under Node 24 (#90…",
        "body": " Fixes a regression under Node 24 on WSL2 where background tool execution triggers a full gateway restart (closes #90428). In `gateway-child.ts`, using `process.kill(-child.pid)` broadcasts signals to the entire process group, causing `SIGTERM` signals to bleed backward into the parent gateway process when managed within a shared `systemd --user` slice context. This patch mitigates the signal bleeding by adding a `child.detached` safety check, ensuring group-wide signaling is only executed if the child is isolated, and falling back safely to a targeted `child.kill(signal)` if the process group context is shared.",
